args: Pop quiz, boss: What are the two things\nevery beach barbecue needs?

Bzzzt! Wrong! ...Well, technically right,
but also generic as hell, so it don't count.
What ya need are crabs and shrimp—
ain't a proper beach BBQ without 'em.
Ain't nothin' beats crisp shellfish\ncooked over a charcoal grill.
Mmm... I bet Cleo would love that.
Then get yer hands ready, because we're\noff to catch some.
...Ah, hell. These little guys are gonna be\ntoo small to throw on the grill.
Is there a way to find bigger ones?

The other day, some old fisherman was
goin' off to me about a special trap
what catches huge crabs and shrimp.
Told me how to make it and everything.
What say we head a little further\noffshore and see if it's true?
Er, but he ALSO may have mentioned\nhow that particular trap is sorta...\nforbidden in these parts.
Er, so is this REALLY a good idea?
Eh, I'm sure it'll be fine. Can't think'a\nany reason it should be banned in the\nfirst place.
Besides, we're doin' this for Cleo.\nNow let's go find us some grub!
I'm still not sure this is a good idea...
Here, help me put this trap together.
So the idea is to lure prey into\nthe cage by putting bait inside?
Damn right. We're gonna have ourselves\na mountain'a shrimp and crabs by the\ntime this baby's finished!
Now we just gotta drop it offshore\nand give it a little time.
Maybe now would be a good time to\ncheck on that trap we set earlier?
The trap's so full of shrimp and crabs\nthat I can't even see the bottom!
Looks like that old fisherman knew\nwhat he was talkin' about.
These crabs have gotta be three times\nthe size of the ones we caught before!
Here, gimme a hand\nand we'll haul 'er up.
Hey! I can't pull this whole thing\nup all by my lonesome!
Quit yer woolgatherin' and gimme a hand!
They must be after our catch!
But these are for Cleo,\nso we ain't givin' 'em up!
Looks like that's the last of 'em.
I guess we know now why people frown\non using that trap—it lures in fiends\nas well as shellfish.
This was a mistake—we should have\nhonored local laws and steered clear.
Yeah, that's on me. Sorry, boss.
Well, at least we got all of these\nbeautiful crabs and shrimp out of it.
And that's more'n enough shellfish.\nTime to hunt down the next ingredient!
